COSMOSformat

Class V2Component

  • java.lang.Object
    • COSMOSformat.COSMOScontentFormat
      • COSMOSformat.V2Component

  • public class V2Component
extends COSMOScontentFormat
    This class extends the COSMOScontentFormat base class to define a V2 record. It defines methods to parse the V2 data array, build a new V2 component from V2 processing results, and convert the V2 component into text for writing out to file.

      • buildV2

        public void buildV2(VFileConstants.V2DataType procType,
                    V2Process inVvals,
                    java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> processSteps)
             throws SmException,
                    FormatException
        This method builds the V2 component from the V2 process object, picking up the data array and updating header parameters and format lines. Once in this method, the V2Process object is no longer needed and its array is transferred to the V2Component object. Use this method when processing V2Processes iteratively. This method includes a parameter representing an array of process steps that were applied to the relative V2Process instance (i.e., inVvals). This parameter is used in liu of using the V2Component's own ProcessStepsRecorder instance to update the comments. The V2Component's ProcessStepsRecorder instance would simply override previous comments with each pass and, thus, would not work correctly when performing iterative processing of V2Processes. Using this method, however, will ensure that a separate set of comments is generated for each V2Process iteration.
        Parameters:
        procType - ACC, VEL, or DIS for the V2 data type
        inVvals - the V2Process object
        processSteps - string array of process steps
        Throws:
        SmException - if unable to access the header values
        FormatException - if unable to format the numeric values to text

      • buildNewDataFormatLine

        public void buildNewDataFormatLine(java.lang.String units,
                                   int unitscode,
                                   java.lang.String dataType,
                                   double timestep)
                            throws SmException
        This method creates a new data format line for the V2 component data array. It calculates the time based on the number of data values and delta t and gets the physical units from the configuration file.
        Parameters:
        units - the numeric code for the type of units, COSMOS table 2
        unitscode - code containing the type of units (cm, cm/sec, etc.)
        dataType - "acceleration", "velocity", or "displacement"
        timestep - the time in seconds between samples
        Throws:
        SmException - if unable to access values in the headers
